@720  = ~*You wake up in Coran's embrace. The elf cups your breast with the easy manner of a man who has caressed many women, and says thoughtfully:* I was born far away from the oceans, and yet I love them as much as the mighty forests or great mountains. Perhaps even more so, because of the feeling of freedom... It is a paradox, because, unless you are of the sea-kin, a fish or kelp, you should feel constrained by the deadly vastness of water.~
