@794  = ~Any adventurer risks dying before his time, Coran.~
@795  = ~It's not like you to lament it, Coran.~
@796  = ~Yes, and that is why I thought that I'd never promise to settle down, my light. Neither could I promise love eternal, nor that I should return after parting.~
@797  = ~Even elven. But I want a life full of adventures and dangers, even if I would not live to tell the tales to bored younglings five hundred years from today. That is why I thought that I'd never promise to settle down, my light. Neither could I promise love eternal, nor that I should return after parting.~
@798  = ~Yes. That might not be such a bad thing, since it makes it unnecessary to worry about our age difference. And, being adventurers, we have a fair chance of dying together, no matter what our life-span is.~
